yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">page 29<=
/a>) says that there will be 1,086 million new Class B shares. Subtract 317=
 million shares issued to Skydance in the merger ($4.75 billion divided by =
$15) and another 100 million issued in the primary share purchase ($1.5 bil=
lion divided by $15) and you get 669 million shares. (<a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35988734.221411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmd=
vdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMDAwMDgxMzgyOC8wMDAwODEzODI4MjQwMD=
AwMjAvcGFyYS0yMDI0MDMzMS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cDee6aceef" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
As of April</a>, Paramount had about 626 million Class B shares outstanding=
, but the number in the investor presentation includes restricted stock uni=
ts.) Multiply that by $15 per share and you get just over $10 billion, whil=
e there=E2=80=99s about $4.3 billion of cash left to pay them out.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-2" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[2] This is sometimes called =E2=80=9C<a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35988734.221411/aHR0cHM6L=
